{"items":[{"title":"Wahlstudien (Election Studies) - Various Years","url_or_doi":"https://gesis.infothek.uni-leipzig.de/portal/en/data/wahlstudien","justification":"GESIS hosts a long-running series of election studies. While spanning multiple decades, datasets from the 1970s are included, offering data on political attitudes, voting behavior, and potentially information related to perceptions of government and political systems. Analysis of these studies could reveal insights into the period."},{"title":"Allensbacher Panel (Allensbach Panel Study) - Various Years","url_or_doi":"https://gesis.infothek.uni-leipzig.de/portal/en/data/allensbacher-panel","justification":"The Allensbach Panel is a longitudinal survey that, while ongoing, has data collected throughout the 1970s. It includes questions on political views, social issues, and attitudes towards government, providing insights into the German political landscape of that era."}, {"title":"Politische Einstellungen und Verhalten (Political Attitudes and Behavior)","url_or_doi":"https://gesis.infothek.uni-leipzig.de/portal/en/data/15569","justification":"This dataset from 1972 focuses specifically on political attitudes and behavior in Germany, offering direct information relevant to the query's timeframe and subject."}, {"title":"Materialien zur Analyse des Wahlverhaltens (Materials for the Analysis of Electoral Behavior)","url_or_doi":"https://gesis.infothek.uni-leipzig.de/portal/en/data/18872","justification":"This collection of materials, while relating to electoral behavior, also includes contextual information about the political environment and governmental factors influencing voter decisions during the 1970s."}, {"title":"Europabarometer - Series","url_or_doi":"https://gesis.infothek.uni-leipzig.de/portal/en/data/europabarometer","justification":"The Eurobarometer series, available through GESIS, includes surveys from the 1970s. While focused on European integration, they also captured data on national political views and trust in government within member states like Germany."}]}
